<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🤖 AI001 Week 6 — English Worksheet</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Debugging — Explaining Errors to AI · <strong>Course:</strong> AI Coding with Replit Agent · <strong>Time:</strong> about 45 minutes</p>
<p>When your code breaks, telling the AI <strong>"it doesn't work"</strong> is not enough. A good bug report gives three things: <strong>what you tried to do</strong>, <strong>what you expected</strong>, and <strong>what actually happened</strong> — plus the exact error message, copied word for word.</p>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read each bug report. Before the AI reads it, decide whether the AI has enough information to help — and what is missing.</p>
<pre><code>It doesn't work. Fix it.
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Does the AI know what "it" is, or what "work" should look like? What is missing?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code>When I click the button, the score should go up,
but nothing happens.
</code></pre>
<p><strong>This says what you tried and what you expected. What one more thing would make it even better?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code>When I click the button the score should go up but nothing
happens. The console shows:
  Uncaught TypeError: Cannot read property 'textContent' of null
  at index.js:7
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Why does pasting the exact error message help the AI find the bug fast?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Fix the Bug Report 🐛</h2>
<p>Each bug report below is missing one of the three parts (what you tried / what you expected / what actually happened) or the error message. Read the situation, then rewrite the report so the AI can help.</p>
<p><strong>Report A</strong> — A button is supposed to <strong>show a message</strong> when clicked, but the page does nothing. The student typed:</p>
<pre><code>The button is broken.
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> add what you expected ("a message should appear") and what actually happened ("nothing happens when I click").</p>
<p><strong>Write a clear bug report:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>What parts did you add?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Report B</strong> — The page shows a red error in the console, but the student only wrote:</p>
<pre><code>There's an error somewhere.
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> copy the exact error message and the line number into the report.</p>
<p><strong>Write a clear bug report (you can invent a sample error message):</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why does the exact message matter?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Report C</strong> — A box was supposed to <strong>stay hidden</strong> until clicked, but it shows the whole time — the opposite of what was wanted.</p>
<pre><code>The box is wrong.
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> explain the opposite situation clearly: "it should be hidden at first, but it is always showing."</p>
<p><strong>Write a clear bug report:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why is describing the "opposite" situation helpful?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Debug Something Real 📸</h2>
<p>Open one of your earlier projects and find a part that does not work the way you want (or ask the AI to add a feature that breaks something). Write a clear bug report with all three parts plus the error message, and let the AI fix it. Then ask: <strong>"What did you change to fix it?"</strong></p>
<p>When you finish, send a <strong>photo or video</strong> of the before and after, then explain what you did. Use these sentence starters — write 4 to 6 sentences total.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>The thing that was broken was …</p>
<p>I expected it to … but instead it …</p>
<p>The error message said …</p>
<p>The AI fixed it by …</p>
<p>In my own words, the bug was …</p>
<p>Next time I hit a bug, I will …</p>
</blockquote>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>4 · Explain the Fix in Your Own Words 🗒️</h2>
<p>The AI told you what it changed. Now write it <strong>in your own words</strong> — like you are explaining to a friend who has never coded. Do not copy the AI's words exactly.</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + a before/after photo (or video) + your own explanation to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
<div class="footer">영어코딩 · <b>english-coding.co.uk</b></div>
</div></body></html>
